<HEADLINE>
ECONOMIC MINISTRY FORMS TASK FORCE TO ENSURE ENERGY SUPPLY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 16 (CNA) 02/16/07  21:26:51 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
State-run enterprises have formed special task forces to address
possible emergency situations during the nine-day Lunar New Year
holiday, which starts Feb. 17, officials from the Ministry of
Economic Affairs (MOEA) said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan Power Company, CPC Corp., Taiwan, and the Taiwan Water
Corp (TWC) have all taken steps to ensure a stable supply of
electricity, oil, and water, during this period, the officials
noted.
</P>
<P>
The power company reminded the public to turn off household
electricity before leaving home for a long vacation during the
holiday.
</P>
<P>
Should a power failure occur during the holiday, the public can
call a hotline at 1911, and the company will send staff to fix
the problem immediately, according to the officials.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the oil company said that 269 of its 651 gas
stations run by private owners around Taiwan will continue to
provide 24-hour service, while adding that stations in scenic
areas will extend their business hours, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Services will return to normal Feb. 23, according to the
officials.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the water company said that people can call a toll free
hotline at 0800-000876 if water supplies are interrupted or
leakage occurs, the officials continued.
</P>
